{{Infobox Magazine |editor = [[Jørgen Dahlgaard]] and [[Carsten Rabæk Kjaer]] |editor_title = Editors |title = Aktuel Naturvidenskab |image_file = AktuelNaturvidenskabForside-3-2009.jpg |image_caption = Cover of the 3rd issue, 2009 (July issue). The main headline reads:''The sun on an erratic course - where are the sunspots?'' |image_alt = Close-up picture of the sun overlaid with the magazine top story headlines. |category = [[Popular science]] |language = [[Danish language|Danish]] |company = Faculty of Science and Technology, [[University of Aarhus]] in cooperation with Danish universities and institutions |country = [[Denmark]] |based = [[Aarhus]] |firstdate = {{start date and age|df=y|1999|4|1}} |frequency = 6 issues per year |circulation_year = 2008 |total_circulation = 8,600 |issn = 1399-2309 |oclc = 609880612 |website = http://aktuelnaturvidenskab.dk }}
'''''Aktuel Naturvidenskab''''' (lit.: ''Current Science'') is a [[Danish language]] [[popular science]] [[magazine]] published in Aarhus, Denmark.
==Profile== ''Aktuel Naturvidenskab'' is published by the Faculty of Science and Technology at the [[University of Aarhus]] in cooperation with Danish universities and institutions. In 2011 it expanded its digital version.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aktuel Naturvidenskab becomes more digital |url=http://medarbejdere.au.dk/en/show/artikel/aktuel-naturvidenskab-becomes-more-digital/ |publisher=Staff.au.dk |accessdate=14 November 2014 |date=16 December 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141225210402/http://medarbejdere.au.dk/en/show/artikel/aktuel-naturvidenskab-becomes-more-digital/ |archivedate=25 December 2014 }}</ref> The magazine mostly provides news on [[natural sciences]].<ref name=snor>{{cite web|title=Media Partners|url=http://sciencenordic.com/about/partners|publisher=ScienceNordic|accessdate=28 February 2015}}</ref> It is one of the media partners of ScienceNordic.<ref name=snor/>
