'''Coffee production in Angola''' refers to the production of [[coffee]] in [[Angola]]. Coffee is one of Angola's largest agricultural products.

Angola was the third largest producer of coffee until 1973 while controlled by [[Portuguese Angola|Portugal]].<ref name="ANGOP2007">{{cite web|url=http://www.portalangop.co.ao/motix/en_us/noticias/economia/Coffee-Production-Angola-Rises-5000-Tons,a8d1cf1c-ce27-41cf-9e7a-c4d46c9229f2.html|title=Coffee Production In Angola Rises To 5000 Tons|date=16 January 2007|publisher=[[ANGOP|Angola News Press]]|accessdate=4 May 2012}}</ref>
Angolan coffee was at its pick of excellency of quality during the presidency of Eurico de Azevedo Noronha of the Instituto do Café de Angola, until his death in 1973. 

==History==
Plantation and production of coffee contributed largely to the economy of Angola's northwestern area, including the [[Uíge Province]].<ref name="ebizguides2008">{{cite book|author=ebizguides|title=Angola: All You Need to Know to Do Business and Have Fun|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T4vvzrSluC8C&pg=PA331|accessdate=4 May 2012|date=January 2008|publisher=MTH Multimedia S.L.|isbn=9788493397883|pages=331–}}</ref> Coffee production was started by the Portuguese in the 1830s and soon became a cash crop; the popular crop grown on approximately 2000 Angolan plantations, owned mostly by the Portuguese, was [[robusta coffee]]. In the 1970s, Angola was one of the largest coffee-producing countries in Africa. However, the civil war for independence from the Portuguese rule devastated the coffee plantations and many coffee agronomists migrated to [[Brazil]], with the coffee plants grown on plantations becoming wild bushes. Rehabilitation of the plantations has been ongoing since 2000, but the investment required to replace the 40-year-old unproductive plants are estimated to be US$230 million. With the opening up of new roads, industrial activity in the province is taking shape.<ref name="Benarde2006">{{cite book|first=Melvin A.|last= Benarde|title=Our precarious habitat?: the sky is not falling|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9O82L8QEZXcC&pg=PA104|accessdate=4 May 2012|year=2006|publisher=Wiley-Interscience|isbn=9780471740650|pages=104–}}</ref>

