{{Infobox language |name=Esimbi |region=Southwestern [[Cameroon]] |speakers=20,000 |date=1982 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=(unknown, perhaps [[Tivoid languages|Tivoid]]) |iso3=ags |glotto=esim1238 |glottorefname=Esimbi }}
'''Esimbi''' is a [[Southern Bantoid]] language of southwestern [[Cameroon]]. It's generally classified as [[Tivoid languages|Tivoid]] but with little evidence; it has just about as much in common with [[Grassfields languages]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rogerblench.info/Language/Niger-Congo/Bantoid/Tivoid/General/Tivoid%20comparative.pdf|title=The Tivoid Languages|last=Blench|first=Roger|date=2010|website=|page=13|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> It is also called '''Isimbi''', '''Simpi''', '''Age''', '''Aage''', '''Bogue''' and '''Mburugam'''.
==References== <references />
{{Languages of Cameroon}} [[Category:Languages of Cameroon]] [[Category:Tivoid languages]] [[Category:Southern Bantoid languages]]
