The year of 2018 was designated to be the '''European Year of Cultural Heritage''' by the [[European Commission]]. <ref>[https://europa.eu/cultural-heritage/ European Year of Cultural Heritage]</ref><ref>[http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_MEMO-17-5066_en.htm European Commission - Fact Sheet - European Year of Cultural Heritage 2018]</ref>
Announced in 2017, it was officially launched on January 31, 2018.<ref>[https://ec.europa.eu/commission/news/annee-europeenne-du-patrimoine-culturel-2018-jan-29_en "President Juncker takes part in the launch of the European Year of Cultural Heritage in Belgium"]</ref>
To this initiative are participating 28 European countries.
