{{Infobox Monument |monument_name = Handaberd |native_name = Հանդաբերդ |image = Handaberd_Fortress.jpg |image_size = |caption = |location = near Knaravan village in Karvachar region, [[Republic of Artsakh]] |designer = |type = Fortress, historically within [[Principality of Khachen]] |material =stone |length = |width = |height = |begin = |complete = 11th century |open = |dedicated_to = |map_image = |map_caption = |map_width = |coordinates = {{coord|40|16|32|N|046|06|20|E|display=title}} |lat = |long = |extra = }}
'''Handaberd''' (Armenian: Հանդաբերդ) is an 11th-century mountain-top fortress built by the rulers of the [[Khachen|Kingdom of Upper Khachen]] and the Kingdom of Tzar (around the village of [[Zar,_Azerbaijan|Zar]]). It is located near Knaravan village in [[Shahumian Province]] of the [[Nagorno-Karabakh Republic]].<ref>Sir Henry Hoyle Howorth. History of the Mongols. Volume 3. p. 86</ref> [http://www.armeniapedia.org/wiki/Handaberd_Fortress]
