{{Infobox Union |name= NLF |country= [[Israel]] |affiliation= Independent |members= |full_name= National Labor Federation in Eretz-Israel |native_name= Histadrut Haovdim Haleumit |image= |founded= 1934 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Tel-Aviv]], Israel |people= Yoav Simhi (Chairman) |website= {{URL|1=http://www.histadrut.net/?categoryId=51903}} |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''National Labor Federation in Eretz-Israel''' (NLF) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[Israel]]. It was founded in 1934 under the basic teachings of [[Theodor Herzl]], [[Max Nordau]], and [[Ze'ev Jabotinsky]]. As opposed to [[Histadrut]], the NLF believes in the separation of employers and trade unions.
ICTUR reports that, although the NLF disclaims political affiliations, it has been seen as sympathetic to [[Likud]]. They are well known because of their original orange and burgundy colors.
==See also== *[[Psagot Investment House]]
