{{Unreferenced|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= Federação de Motociclismo de Portugal |abbrev = FMP |logo= |sport=[[Motorsport]] |founded = |aff = |affdate = |region = |regionyear = | image = | size = | caption = | category = | jurisdiction = [[Portugal]] | year closed = | headquarters = [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]] | president = Dr. Jorge Pessanha Viegas | chairman = | key staff = |chiefexec = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url =www.fnm.pt |countryflag=POR |countryflag2= }} The '''Portuguese Motorcycling Federation''' (FMP) (Portuguese: Federação de Motociclismo de Portugal; FMP) is the governing body of Motorcycling in Portugal. It is based in the capital city of Lisbon.
It organises the Portuguese racing championships, which interests are: Enduro, Cross Country, Quad Cross, Motocross, Supercross, Offroad, SuperMoto, Stunt Riding, Trial and Road racing.
Besides racing, it covers several non-competitive activities like managing affiliated Clubs rallies calendar and events such as [[Portugal de Lés a Lés]].
