{{Infobox book | name = Požganica | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:Pozganica book cover.jpg | caption = Cover of book | author = [[Prežihov Voranc]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = {{flag|Slovenia}} | language = [[Slovenian language|Slovenian]] | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = | pub_date = | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = | isbn = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Požganica''''' is a novel by [[Slovenia]]n author [[Prežihov Voranc]]. It was first published in 1939,<ref name="Tuma1997">{{cite book|last=Tuma|first=Henrik|title=Iz mojega življenja: spomini, misli in izpovedi|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LX__-dTeed4C&pg=PA476|accessdate=19 July 2012|year=1997|publisher=Zalozba Tuma d.o.o|isbn=978-961-6245-03-6|page=476}}</ref> but was based on a short story first published in 1920. The author presents the work happening in [[Carinthia]] after the First World War with the Carinthian Plebiscite and, consequently, the fate of the Carinthian Slovenes under Austria.
