Tzofei [[Tel Aviv]] (or Tel Aviv Scouts<ref name="kesher-06">[http://www.mjds.net/Kesher2005_2006/04_28_2006.pdf Kesher Connection], April 28, 2006, page 9. Retrieved February 18, 2007</ref> in [[English language|English]]) is a musical group originating from Israel.  The performers are teenagers, picked out of the Israel Scouts in Tel-Aviv, Israel. They tour around the world, performing mostly [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] songs for [[Judaism|Jewish]] organizations and others the world over. For example, they performed [[Yom Ha'atzmaut]] concerts in [[Lima]] and [[Guayaquil]] in June 2003,<ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=es&u=http://www.kh-uia.org.il/newhotline/KEREN_HOY/KEREN%2520HOY%252007.htm&oi=translate Translated version of Keren Today]</ref> as they did in [[St. Louis Park, MN]], in 2006.<ref name="kesher-06"/> The group's musical director is Moishele Yosef, who has various other jobs in the musical profession.<ref name="btnli3">[http://www.chetz-vkeshet.org.il/newsletter/newsletter-3.pdf Ba'Tzofim Newsletter, Issue 3], retrieved February 18, 2007</ref>

